But their stubborn hearts, defiled by fleshly lusts, proved the oracles of the prophet by the decision of their unbelief. Yet the servant of God returned to the lodging where the sacristanl of the church had received him, and made known the day and hour of imminent destruction. “ I go in haste,” he said, “ from a stubborn town that shall swiftly perish.'' Then he went away to the next town, which is called Comagem's.2 This was very strictly guarded by the barbarians established within, who had entered into a league³ with the Romans, and it was not easy for any one to secure permission to go in or to leave. Yet, though they knew him not, they neither questioned the servant of God, nor turned him back. So anon he went into the church ; and when he found all in despair
